Tottenham Hotspur manager, Jose Mourinho has decided to battle Premier League rival, Manchester United for Leicester City defender, Ricardo Pereira. According to Express UK, Mourinho has his heart set on the right-back and wants Spurs to sign Pereria for £30million. The newspaper claimed that Man United are also interested in signing the 26-year-old from Leicester. The Portugal international could be Mourinho’s first signing this January as he prepares to bolster his team for the second half of the season. Pereria joined Leicester from Porto in a £21million deal in 2018. He won Leicester’s Player of the Season in his first year at the club. His current contract with the Foxes will end in 2023.